content:
In CRM Analytics, connect disconnected nodes or branches to join or append data from any node to any other node in a Data Prep recipe. You can also create a branch at an intermediate node, and join or append it to another path in the recipe.

To create a branch and join or append it to another path, hover over a node to see the Branch button. Then drag the Branch button on top of a node in the other path.

In the Connect Nodes box, select whether to join or append the data. To join or append data to another node, drag the Add Node button for a node or a Branch button on top of the predecessor.

Then select whether to join or append the data in the Connect Nodes box. This graph joins aggregated account data back to the account records.

To make the flow of data easier to view, reposition the recipe nodes in the graph. Select and move individual nodes, or drag your mouse to select as many nodes as you want. Pull the group of nodes around to rearrange, or delete them all at once.
title: Connecting and Reorganizing Nodes in CRM Analytics
